so called because, out of charity, they allow widows to marry one more
husband, and the M      nukattu, who permit a woman to have three
husbands in succession.        They are also said to recognise, among
themselves, four sub-divisions, Vokkiliyan (cultivator), M      ru
Balayan      ru (three bangle people), Bottu Katt      ru (bottu tying
people), Vokkuloth      ru, to the last of which the following notes
mainly refer.
